18:04.160 --> 18:08.520
Science Fiction author Kevin O'Donnell Jr. has written many short stories plus six novels today.

18:09.000 --> 18:10.400
Three of his novels form a series.

18:10.400 --> 18:16.840
The series is called The Journeys of McGill Fee and the three installments are subtitled Caverns, Reefs and Lava.

18:17.180 --> 18:23.660
McGill Fee is a 21st century earthling who at age four days is swallowed by a mysterious, giant, amoebillite gastropod,

18:24.300 --> 18:27.920
which was sent by the even more mysterious far being Rhett's Glorin.

18:28.540 --> 18:32.900
The infant McGill remains in the gastropod precisely 71 hours and 24 minutes.

18:33.340 --> 18:36.540
Then he is discharged and the gastropod leaves the earth with no comment.

18:36.840 --> 18:38.620
McGill seems to be a normal lad.

18:38.620 --> 18:45.720
At age five, however, it is discovered that he has the flinger talent, the extremely rare ability to transmit people or objects

18:45.720 --> 18:52.520
instantaneously to distant destinations in the galaxy, providing the total mass of any load doesn't exceed 918 kilograms.

18:53.060 --> 18:58.240
Young McGill is enrolled in the Flinger Academy where he masters the art under the tutelage of experienced flingers.

18:58.540 --> 19:01.040
Then at age 17 he is certified as a flinger.

19:01.320 --> 19:06.420
But since McGill has puzzled about the motive of the far being for having the gastropod swallow him for three days,

19:06.420 --> 19:09.360
he vows to seek out the far being and ask him why.

19:09.800 --> 19:12.560
Another group is interested in McGill too, the organization.

19:13.140 --> 19:17.040
They reason that if the far being has something in store for McGill, then they want it too.

19:17.360 --> 19:18.180
The stage is set.

19:18.520 --> 19:23.260
Young McGill is mastering flinging while simultaneously learning about such things in life as romance,

19:23.780 --> 19:27.080
trying to live with the flinger bureaucracy and searching for the far being.

19:27.480 --> 19:30.040
All the while the sinister organization is after him.

19:30.480 --> 19:33.220
The series is obviously humorous, but it's serious as well.

19:33.220 --> 19:35.860
Hero Donald comments on his intention for the series.

19:36.500 --> 19:48.200
Well, my primary intent in the McGill fan series is to do something in life, fast-paced, adventuresome,

19:49.220 --> 19:59.100
that nonetheless shows a person of incredible talent growing up and the problems he faces.

20:02.740 --> 20:10.500
That aspect of attempts to take lower priority and the adventures of McGill being come first.

20:11.280 --> 20:17.360
I do want a book that people can sit down and read quickly and really enjoy.

20:17.880 --> 20:21.100
It's not a gloomy book.

20:21.920 --> 20:26.160
The Andrew Snatch and War of Omission are sort of downbeat books.

20:27.060 --> 20:34.080
Nape Lines is in a way upbeat, but it's got a lot of depressing stuff in it.

20:34.700 --> 20:36.440
Whereas McGill's fan is not.

20:38.860 --> 20:45.940
I do it partly to change the pace, to write a book that just moves right along with the art of finish.

20:45.940 --> 20:48.500
There's a lot of things happening.

20:49.580 --> 20:55.620
He has a very clear-cut hero who isn't unless human, has his problems.

20:56.540 --> 21:02.420
In the first book, Caverns, McGill takes charge of a ron-gon egg which hatches in book two, Reefs.

21:02.760 --> 21:07.400
He names the young reptilian ron-gon Sam, and Sam becomes McGill's sidekick.

21:07.720 --> 21:09.640
Hero Donald comments on Sam's role.

21:10.280 --> 21:13.020
Of course Sam, he's going to grow up so mixed up.

21:13.920 --> 21:19.220
Because he's being raised entirely on earth, well except for their excursions off-world.

21:19.360 --> 21:24.680
But he's being raised by a human being with very human values. But Sam is not human.

21:25.640 --> 21:35.100
When he gets to his tips to maturity, he's going to be, oh heavens, from the tip of his nose to the tip of his tail, he's going to be about 15 feet long.

21:36.100 --> 21:39.940
And he can stand about, oh, what, four and a half feet high at the shoulder?

21:41.180 --> 21:47.220
There's the back part of him, and his head will be pretty much about six feet off the ground.

21:47.540 --> 21:50.180
I mean, he's going to be big. He's going to be very alien-looking.

21:52.000 --> 21:56.860
And he's going to have a lot of trouble because he's neither one nor the other.

21:57.640 --> 22:02.540
He's not a ron-gon. He knows nothing of ron-gon culture.

22:03.600 --> 22:07.140
But he's not, and can never be a human being.

22:09.840 --> 22:13.080
I see lots of interesting problems ahead for Sam.

