Kevin O'Donnell Jr.'s Science Fiction Series, The Journeys of McGill Fee and His Highly Popular Adventure Yarn, Featuring the Young Flinger McGill Fee and,

24:02.600 --> 24:05.360
Who, after having developed his talent, is searching for the far-being.

24:05.740 --> 24:11.340
Not only must young Fee and Cope with his talent and life in general, he must avoid being captured by the organization.

24:11.340 --> 24:19.900
The series is humorous, but interspersed among the action and humor are the violent deaths of many of McGill's allies and friends, including his parents, his lovers, and his roommates.

24:20.560 --> 24:24.020
We asked O'Donnell why he so freely dispatches with most of McGill's acquaintances.

24:24.940 --> 24:27.980
Part of that is cold calculation on my part.

24:28.700 --> 24:37.700
That when you're writing a series, one of the real difficulties is convincing the reader that your hero is in danger.

24:38.180 --> 24:42.120
When you write one book, there's no problem, because the reader doesn't know how it's going to come out.

24:42.400 --> 24:51.600
But when you have a series, the reader says, well, hey, look, you know, he's been through 18 of these adventures now, and he's emerged on the gauge from everyone, so why worry?

24:52.120 --> 24:55.440
And, you know, the reader's emotional involvement in the story is lessened.

24:55.680 --> 25:06.580
But when it is a real danger, when people near and dear to them are dying, and in some cases dying horribly, it brings the threat much closer,

25:06.580 --> 25:07.680
and it makes it much more plausible.

25:09.820 --> 25:14.040
And at this point, McGill has lost a lot of people who are very close to him.

25:14.920 --> 25:19.480
His parents, Nadia, and Braestine, he's going to lose more.

25:21.280 --> 25:30.760
You know, as I say, part of it is cold calculation, but part of it is also realistic appraisal of the situation being him.

25:30.760 --> 25:41.660
He's got this talent, he's got this mysterious link with this even more mysterious alien being, and he has people hot on his trail.

25:44.260 --> 25:54.760
And it brings, you know, reader's credibility to have not only him, but all his friends coming to you safe and sound every time.

25:54.760 --> 26:03.020
You know, the organization, they may not be perfect, but they're not total amateurs, and they're going to be striking real close to home.

26:04.900 --> 26:09.400
And they have so far in the first three books, and they'll continue to.

26:10.200 --> 26:13.020
McGill encounters several types of aliens on his journeys.

26:13.460 --> 26:16.960
We ask O'Donnell for what purpose does he use alien characters in the series?

26:16.960 --> 26:22.740
In the series, I'm trying to make aliens who are comprehensible.

26:24.880 --> 26:27.180
And yet who are not human.

26:28.040 --> 26:37.020
I really think when we run into alien species, and sooner or later we will, they will have traits which we recognize as traits that we have.

26:38.620 --> 26:43.860
In lava, I've got these religious fanatics running around.

26:45.880 --> 26:57.640
I suspect that any sentient race we encounter will, at least in one stage of their development, have gone through an intensely religious period.

26:57.640 --> 27:10.280
But like still be religious today, if you can tell, but I think any sentient being has to wonder on its origin, how it came to be, why it came to be, who created the universe.

27:12.000 --> 27:27.660
So, you know, I'm trying to, not to mirror humanity, but to suggest that there are alternates with which we can have traits, attitudes in Donnell.

27:28.380 --> 27:34.760
So far, O'Donnell has written three books in the McGill-Phean series. Here's what O'Donnell said when we asked him if there would be any more in the series.

27:34.760 --> 27:46.600
Yes, definitely. At the moment is a McGill story, and from his childhood just been published in Berkeley Showcase.

27:48.480 --> 27:53.900
There will be more being books.

27:53.900 --> 28:03.620
At the moment, I'm saying seven more in the series will end soon. I'm glad to at least attend.

28:04.540 --> 28:09.800
Kevin O'Donnell Jr. will keep us entertained with the adventures of McGill-Phean for at least a while longer.

